<title>UK: BTR shares rise after restructuring news.</title>
<headline>BTR shares rise after restructuring news.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in BTR Plc rose after the industrial conglomerate outlined a long-awaited restructuring plan, selling low-growth businesses with sales of 2.3 billion stg and cutting its first-half dividend to 4.0p from 5.6p.</p>
<p>The stock was up 5-1/2p at 271-1/2 by 0702 GMT.</p>
<p>&quot;My reading is that it is a satisfactory statement and that there is enough for the market to be reasonably happy with,&quot; said one senior sales trader.</p>
<p>&quot;The dividend cut was expected and the rapidity with which BTR wants to get on with the strategic review will be seen as encouraging.&quot;</p>
